422
00:18:06,770 --> 00:18:09,810
Let’s just wait and see.

423
00:18:11,770 --> 00:18:12,530
Mr. Sun.

424
00:18:12,660 --> 00:18:15,500
The memorial to the throne you wrote
is not profound enough.

425
00:18:16,180 --> 00:18:17,220
His Majesty won’t feel like
he is on the scene

426
00:18:17,220 --> 00:18:19,220
after he hears it.

427
00:18:19,530 --> 00:18:22,090
And he won’t feel the anger about
Baroness Ban holding him in contempt

428
00:18:22,330 --> 00:18:25,050
and whipping an imperial officer
in public.

429
00:18:25,380 --> 00:18:26,380
You should change it.

430
00:18:26,380 --> 00:18:26,980
All right.

431
00:18:26,980 --> 00:18:28,140
Make it more profound.

432
00:18:28,250 --> 00:18:28,940
Okay.

433
00:18:35,460 --> 00:18:36,530
Mr. Li.

434
00:18:36,530 --> 00:18:37,090
Yeah.

435
00:18:37,090 --> 00:18:39,980
Your memorial to the throne
is not sensational enough.

436
00:18:41,050 --> 00:18:42,250
It’s too dull.

437
00:18:42,380 --> 00:18:43,810
It sounds like it has
nothing to do with you.

438
00:18:43,980 --> 00:18:46,250
Well, imagine

439
00:18:46,250 --> 00:18:47,660
that your son was beaten half to death.

440
00:18:47,810 --> 00:18:49,660
Now he is lying in bed.

441
00:18:49,770 --> 00:18:52,460
You are going to write
a memorial to the throne to His Majesty

442
00:18:52,570 --> 00:18:54,010
to seek justice for your son.

443
00:18:54,570 --> 00:18:56,220
You must write it in a tearful tone.

444
00:18:56,850 --> 00:18:59,380
That makes it profound and sensational.

445
00:18:59,530 --> 00:19:00,740
But, Your Grace, I...

446
00:19:00,740 --> 00:19:02,090
I don’t have a son. Do you forget it?

447
00:19:02,810 --> 00:19:04,290
It’s not a problem
that you don’t have a son.

448
00:19:04,290 --> 00:19:05,050
Do you have parents?

449
00:19:05,250 --> 00:19:06,570
Just imagine that happening
to your parents!

450
00:19:06,660 --> 00:19:07,420
Yeah.

451
00:19:08,330 --> 00:19:09,530
I’ll try my best.

452
00:19:09,740 --> 00:19:10,660
Mr. Song.

453
00:19:10,770 --> 00:19:12,740
Yours should be perfect, right?

454
00:19:18,570 --> 00:19:19,460
Mr. Song.

455
00:19:21,090 --> 00:19:22,140
I remember

456
00:19:22,740 --> 00:19:25,460
you were among the top ten talents
in the imperial examination.

457
00:19:25,700 --> 00:19:27,420
Yeah.

458
00:19:27,420 --> 00:19:29,180
Why are there so many wrong words

459
00:19:29,700 --> 00:19:31,010
